x4freetext: Spectroscopically pure (99.99%) Tm and Ta foils of
thickness 30 mg/cm2 and 57 mg/cm2, respectively, were
interspersed with Al foils varying thickness which
act as energy degraders, while bismuth targets of
thickness 1 mg/cm2 were prepared by vacuum
evaporation technique from highly specpure Bi metal
deposited on an Al backing of thickness 6.7 mg/cm2.
95 cm3 coaxial Ge (Li) detector having a
resolution of 2.0 keV for 1332 keV photons of 60Co,
coupled to a CANBERRA-88 multichannel analyser.
